  "text": "But the method's robustness or behavior has been assessed in various aspects (e.g. Broquet et al. 68 2006b; Leblois et al. 2003; Leblois et al. 2004; Vekemans & Hardy 2004; [CITATION_1] , and it relies on manageable sampling requirements. Accordingly, interpretations of isolation-by-distance 70 patterns are frequent in the literature, including several estimations of the dispersal parameter σ (reviewed in Table S1 , supplementary material. See also Fig. 1) . 72 [CITATION_2] or between groups of individuals (either because the population under study is sub-74 divided into discrete units, or because discrete groups of individuals were sampled from an otherwise continuous population; [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Hereafter we will use the words \"individual\" 76 and \"group\" to refer to the sampling unit of each approach. The two methods are based on the same theoretical background (detailed in Rousset 2004 ) and aim at estimating exactly the same quantity. 78",
